  "prompt": "How does AdMob know if your app violates their ToS?",
  "response": "AdMob uses several methods to detect potential Terms of Service (ToS) violations:\n\n1. Automated Scanning\n- Analyzes app code and behavior\n- Checks for prohibited ad implementation\n- Detects invalid click patterns\n- Uses machine learning algorithms\n\n2. User Reports\n- Allows users to flag suspicious app behavior\n- Receives direct feedback about inappropriate content\n\n3. Manual Review\n- Periodic human reviews of apps\n- Checks apps during initial submission\n- Random spot-checks of existing apps\n\n4. Traffic Analysis\n- Monitors ad click patterns\n- Detects unusual or fraudulent traffic\n- Tracks invalid interaction metrics\n\n5. SDK Integration Checks\n- Verifies correct AdMob SDK implementation\n- Ensures compliance with integration guidelines\n\n6. Automated Crawler/Bot Detection\n- Identifies non-human interactions\n- Prevents artificial traffic inflation\n\nCommon violations they look for:\n- Fake clicks\n- Prohibited content\n- Click farming\n- Improper ad placement\n- Incentivized ad interactions\n- Misleading ad implementations\n\nIf violations are detected, consequences can range from warning notifications to ad revenue suspension or account termination.",
